Interface Zones

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, ZonesTypes
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ZonesStub

    public interface Zones
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, ZonesTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Zones interface provides methods to manage consumption-domain zones. This interface was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

      • list

        Zones.ListInvocation list()
        Returns information about the zones available on this vCenter server, where the zones need to match ZonesTypes.FilterSpec. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        Invocation Result:
        The list of zones available on this vCenter that match the criteria specified in ZonesTypes.FilterSpec.

        Returns:
        instance of Zones.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Unauthorized - if the user doesn't have all of the privileges described as follows: - The resource com.vmware.vcenter.consumption_domains.Zone referenced by the parameter zones in FilterSpec requires System.Read privilege.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Error - when unexpected error is encountered.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires System.Read.

      • create

        Zones.CreateInvocation create(ZonesTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Creates a zone based on the provided specifications. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        Invocation Result:
        The identifier of the created zone. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.consumption_domains.Zone.

        Parameters:
        spec - Specifications for the zone to be created.
        Returns:
        instance of Zones.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        AlreadyExists - if a zone with the same identifier already exists in this vCenter server.
        InvalidArgument - if any of the input information in the createSpec is invalid.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user doesn't have Zones.Manage privilege.
        Error - when unexpected error is encountered.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires Zone.Manage.

      • delete

        Zones.DeleteInvocation delete(java.lang.String zone)
        Deletes the zone with the specified identifier. In order to delete a zone, there must not be any workload running in that zone because deleting the zone without removing all the dependencies on that zone can cause undefined behavior for the entities depending on this zone to be present. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.
        Parameters:
        zone - Identifier of the zone to be deleted. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.consumption_domains.Zone.
        Returns:
        instance of Zones.DeleteInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described delete operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if no zone with the specified identifier is found in this vCenter server.
        NotAllowedInCurrentState - if there is a workload running in the specified zone and depends on this zone to be present.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user doesn't have all of the privileges described as follows: - The resource com.vmware.vcenter.consumption_domains.Zone referenced by the parameter zone requires Zones.Manage privilege.
        Error - when unexpected error is encountered.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires Zone.Manage.
